               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420919-name-721" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420919-name-721" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420919-name-721" type="surname" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420919-name-721" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM ABRAHAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a law-stationer's shop in the Middle Temple. On the 9th of September, between five and six o' clock in the afternoon, the prisoner came for half a quire of paper—I served him—he tendered me a 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. piece, which I detected to be counterfeit—I asked if he knew it was bad—he said, "No"—I asked who he came from—he said, "Mr. Pontifex"—as I knew Mr. Pontifex, I offered to send our shopman. down with him to ascertain the truth of his statement—he then said he did not come from Mr. Pontifex, but he had formerly been with Mr. Pontifex—I sent for a policeman, and during that time the prisoner said he hoped I should not be too hard with him—I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420919-name-722" type="witnessName">
