                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 325.) I took the prisoner—I searched him, but found no more money on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where did you find him? Mr. Abraham's shop—as I was taking him from Guildhall, he said he had no other means of getting a livelihood, but by passing bad money—this was after he was committed.</p>
